The '''Isle of Man Incinerator''' was designed by Savage & Chadwick Architects and is notable for its unusual shape and design, the [[flue gas stack|stack]] of which is designed to represent a Viking sail. [[Suez Recycling and Recovery UK|SUEZ Recycling and Recovery UK]] was awarded the contract to design build and operate the [[incinerator]] by the [[Isle of Man Government]]. The incinerator is located on an old disused [[landfill]] and has a capacity to treat 60,000 tonnes of [[municipal waste]] in addition to [[clinical waste|clinical]] and [[animal by-products|animal waste]]. In order to accomplish this the facility actually incorporates two separate incinerators. The facility uses [[Incineration#Fixed or moving grate combustion|moving grate technology]].

