{{Infobox company |name = National Gas Company of Trinidad and Tobago |logo = |logo_size = |type = [[Public company|Public]] | |traded_as = |foundation = 1975 |location_city = [[Point Lisas|Orinoco Drive, Point Lisas Industrial Estate]], [[Couva]] |location_country = [[Trinidad and Tobago]] |location = <!--modifies "Headquarters" entry--> |locations = <!--# of locations--> |key_people = |area_served = |industry = Natural Gas |products = Natural Gas |services = |revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |num_employees = |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |homepage = [https://ngc.co.tt/ www.ngc.co.tt] |dissolved = |footnotes = }}
The '''National Gas Company of Trinidad and Tobago Limited (NGC)''' is a state-owned natural gas company. It was created by the Government of [[Trinidad and Tobago]] in 1975. NGC is operating in the field of gas pipelines, industrial sites, gas production, port and marine infrastructure, natural gas liquids and liquefied natural gas. It has assets worth $43 billion. Its credit rating by Moody's is Baa2 [https://www.moodys.com/research/Moodys-downgrades-NGCs-ratings-to-Baa2-changes-outlooks-to-negative--PR_322925] and A- from S&P [http://news.co.tt/public_html/article.php?story=20150305104128788] The company currently operates in [[Point Lisas]], [[Couva]] at the Point Lisas Industrial Estate.
