'''''The Hand of Franklin'''''<ref>{{cite web|title=Explore Magazine review of The Hand of Franklin|url=http://www.explore-mag.com/The_Happy_Camper_Frank_Wolfs_new_film_The_Hand_of_Franklin/}}</ref> is a 2015 [[Canada|Canadian]] documentary film by [[Frank Wolf (filmmaker)|Frank Wolf]] that follows a four-person team attempting to row the [[Northwest Passage]] in order to shed light on [[climate change in the Arctic]].<ref>{{cite web|title=CBS News Interview|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/videos/arctic-rowers-bring-attention-to-climate-change/}}</ref> The film won the award for 'Best Documentary Feature' at the 2016 Ramunas Atelier International Film Awards,<ref>{{cite web|title=2016 RAIFF winners|url=http://www.ramuno-atelje.lt/index.php/raiifa}}</ref> won for 'Best Canadian Film' at the 2015 Vancouver International Mountain Film Festival (VIMFF)<ref>{{cite web|title=VIMFF 2015 Award Winners|url=http://www.vimff.org/films/vimff_film_awards_2015/|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150225035312/http://www.vimff.org/films/vimff_film_awards_2015/|archivedate=2015-02-25|df=}}</ref> and won the 'Adventure Award' at the 2016 [[San Francisco International Ocean Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2016 SFIOFF Award Winners|url=http://oceanfilmfest.org/news/2016/2/12/2016-awards}}</ref> It features music by Peirson Ross, The Cyrillic Typewriter, Sylvia Cloutier and [[Madeleine Allakariallak]] and airs in Canada on CBC's ''[[documentary (TV channel)|documentary]]'' channel.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Hand of Franklin on CBC's documentary channel|url=http://www.cbc.ca/documentarychannel/feature-programs/the_hand_of_franklin/}}</ref> {{Portal|Global warming}}
